  1. Preparing. Loading libraries, set seed and working directory.
library(ggplot2)
library(caret)
## Loading required package: lattice
set.seed(123)
setwd("/Users/mamadashi/Data sciense/pml/R")
  1. Reading data.
data <- read.csv("pml-training.csv")
predict <- read.csv("pml-testing.csv")
  1. Spliting data into training/test
index <- createDataPartition(y = data$classe, p = 0.95, list = FALSE)
train <- data[index,]
test <- data[-index,]
  1. Analyse dataset. Identification of near zero variance predictors.
  nzv <- nearZeroVar(train, saveMetrics = TRUE)
  subset(nzv, nzv==FALSE)

  1. Building some models on training set. Use “k-nearest neighbors” method as most suitable for classification. Model 1. Use some predictors that looks like more valuable
fit1 <-  train(classe ~ roll_belt+
               pitch_belt+
               yaw_belt+
               roll_forearm+
               pitch_forearm+
               yaw_forearm+
               roll_arm+
               pitch_arm+
               yaw_arm
             , data = data, method = "knn")
fit1

Model 3. Using preprocessing.

fit3 <- train(classe ~ roll_belt+
               pitch_belt+
               yaw_belt+
               roll_forearm+
               pitch_forearm+
               yaw_forearm+
               roll_dumbbell+
               pitch_dumbbell+
               yaw_dumbbell+
               roll_arm+
               pitch_arm+
               yaw_arm
             , data = train, method = "knn", preProcess =
               c("center","scale"))

6.Test with test data.

Model 3 is the best one, so test it with test data.

cm <- confusionMatrix(r, test$classe)
